#Text=Ethiopian troops will leave Somalia
#Text=A foreign ministry spokesperson has announced that all Ethiopian troops will withdraw from Somalia by the end of this year .
#Text=Two years ago , Ethiopia sent out thousands of soldiers to Somalia in an effort to help the government oust Islamists from the Somali capital of Mogadishu .

#Text=Under the deal , African Union troops will replace Ethiopian troops withdrawing from the cities of Mogadishu and Beledweyne , while the Somali government and ARS will create a police force 10,000-strong .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Ethiopian troops to leave Somalia " — BBC News Online , November 29 , 2008

column1: #Text=Poll results spark riots in Nigerian city
#Text=This story has updates
#Text=See Riots in Nigeria kill around 400 , November 30 , 2008
#Text=According to aid workers , at least twenty people , including a policeman , have been killed in riots in the Nigerian city of Jos after local elections .
#Text=Muslim opposition supporters started rioting when they heard that their candidate to head the council had been defeated .
#Text=A dusk-to-dawn curfew has been imposed by the authorities , and soldiers have been deployed to the streets when rival gangs started burning churches and mosques .
#Text=According to the Red Cross , no less than twenty people have been killed and about 300 wounded as a result of the unrest , and at least ten thousand more have been forced from their homes .
#Text=About 100 homes have been burnt .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Poll riots erupt in Nigerian city " — BBC News Online , November 29 , 2008
#Text=" Clashes kill at least 20 in Nigerian city of Jos " — Bester News , November 29 , 2008
#Text=" Riots kill ' hundreds ' in Nigeria " — BBC News Online , November 29 , 2008
#Text=Suicide bomber in Iraqi mosque kills 12
#Text=A suicide bomber blew himself up in an Iraqi mosque on Friday , killing twelve people and injuring a further sixteen .
#Text=The attack happened at a Shiite mosque in the Musayyib district in Babil , located 100 kilometres south of Iraq 's capital Baghdad .
#Text=This comes a day after the Iraqi parliament approved a deal with the United States to start withdrawing US troops from the country .
#Text=Under the timetable , soldiers will start leaving Iraqi streets in June of 2009 and leave the country completely by the end of 2011 .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Suicide bombing at Iraqi mosque " — BBC News Online , November 29 , 2008
#Text=" Suicide bombing at mosque in Iraq kills 12 , injures 16 " — The Earth Times , November 29 , 2008
#Text=British trainee police arrested for suspected drugs offences
#Text=File : Metropolitan Police Flag . gif
#Text=The officers were training at a Metropolitan Police training centre
#Text=Image : Sancho .
#Text=( Image missing from commons : image ; log )
#Text=Two British trainee police officers have been arrested for suspected possession of Class A drugs .
#Text=One of the two women involved were arrested after being taken to hospital at the start of this month , while the other was arrested on charges of possession with intention to supply .
#Text=Both have been released on bail .
#Text=Before their arrest , the women were training in Hendon , London , in a centre run by the Metropolitan Police .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Trainee police officers arrested " — BBC News Online , November 29 , 2008
